node.text: There were more out LGBTQ+ athletes competing in the #Tokyo2020 Olympics than at any other Games in history! The folks at @proctergamble invited me (and a bunch of amazing individuals) to speak on the importance of representation and on athletes using their voice to uplift their communities. You can check out the conversations via the link in bio! That’s not all though – P&G also made a $100K commitment to @athleteally to further their efforts around LGBTQ+ education, sport policy reform and athlete activism. Such a meaningful donation will drive positive change in an effort to create a more inclusive world for all. #LeadWithLove #PGPartner ✨♥️

node.text: I can only imagine the immense pressure that Simone Biles felt going into tonight’s team event with the weight of a country on her shoulders, the whole world watching and all eyes on her. “The greatest of all time” would be a merciless title to have to live up to over and over again. She ended up withdrawing from the competition and I just want to say that I’m sincerely proud of her for doing so. It took tremendous courage for her to listen to her instincts and choose preservation (both mental and physical) instead of being caught up in all of the noise. I’m also truly proud of the rest of the young women on Team USA for adapting and persevering to earn Olympic silver! Congratulations ladies, I feel honored to have witnessed it!!! #Tokyo2020

node.text: Back home in LA after a great week in Aspen for the @XGames. I'm incredibly grateful to the folks at @ESPN for putting on a COVID safe event when the pandemic has cancelled pretty much all of our other competitions so far this season. I didn't quite have the performance that I was hoping for but my body was a wreck and I'm proud of myself for battling through the injuries and putting down a run - even if it wasn't my best one ever. In awe of the level of skiing showcased this past weekend and feeling inspired and motivated to put my nose to the grindstone to step my run up for the next event (wherever/ whenever that may be). Big thanks to @monsterenergy @prada and @hoteljeromeaspen for taking such great care of me this weekend and to my coach @justin_dorey for all of the help and support!
